/*!
\page lorenz_model Lorenz model

The Lorenz model is a 3-dimensional chaotic system. The equations of the model are:

<center>
\f$\partial_tx = Pr (y - x)\f$<br>
\f$\partial_ty = x (Ra - z) -y\f$ <br>
\f$\partial_tz = xy - b z\f$  <br>
</center>

where \f$Pr\f$ is the Prandtl number, \f$Ra\f$ the Rayleigh number, and \f$b\f$ is positive number.

The Lorenz model is implemented in <code>Lorenz.hxx</code> and <code>Lorenz.cxx</code>. The class \link Verdandi::Lorenz Lorenz\endlink is a template class: <code>Lorenz<T></code>. <code>T</code> is the numerical type of the variables (e.g., <code>double</code>).

The state vector is \f$(x, y, z)\f$.

*/
